<div1 xml:lang="en" type="document">

<pb n="Roll5-1299.jpg"/>

<note>Department of State Received May <del>25</del> 24 1888</note>

<p>Hampton Va<lb/>
May 23 /88</p>

<p>Hon. G. L. Rives<lb/>
Assistant Secretary of State<lb/>
Washington D.C.</p>

<p>Sir:</p>

<p>Yours of the <unclear>10th</unclear> inst. came
duly to hand and I was more
than glad that items of
disallowances made against
me had your careful consideration.
Am I to understand
that "Items of disallowances 4, 9,
and 11, for messenger service
and for such portion of items 15
<unclear extent="one word"/> is made up of compensation
<unclear>for</unclear> messenger" may be drawn
<unclear>by</unclear> me, which above amount
is $75.50/100. Shall I draw for
the same? Please inform
me. I feel contented with

<pb n="Roll5-1300.jpg"/>

your judgement in my
use, but please your honor
inform Mrs. Hopkins officially
that what she expects the
Department of State to pay me
<unclear extent="one word"/> involve upon her to do so for
the burial of her husband,
Moses A. Hopkins.</p>

<p>I have the honor to be, Sir,<lb/>
Yours Truly<lb/>
Sam'l S. Sevier</p>

<p>Address 57 South St.<lb/>
New York</p>

</div1>

